[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The voice is excellent throughout. The opening scenario (14,000 heart failure patients who all get the same treatment but respond differently) is immediately compelling. The progression from clinical intuition ("cardiologists know this") to the technical challenge ("there are no labels") is masterfully paced. The Technology section is one of the best in the cookbook: it teaches clustering from first principles without condescending, covers algorithm tradeoffs with genuine nuance, and the validation discussion is intellectually honest.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Specific highlights:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - "The 'might' is doing a lot of work in that sentence, and we'll come back to it." (Perfect parenthetical aside)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - "Feature selection is the entire ballgame." (Punchy, memorable)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - "The subtypes are not 'in the data' waiting to be discovered. They're a function of which data you choose to look at and how you represent it." (This is the key insight, delivered perfectly)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The Honest Take section is genuinely self-deprecating: "I've seen teams spend months on sophisticated clustering algorithms only to realize their features were dominated by age and sex."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The 70/30 vendor balance is well-maintained. The entire Technology section (which is substantial) is vendor-agnostic. AWS appears only in the implementation half.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
